title: "Tesla: Cost-Cutting Pressure Will Continue To Rise Due To China"
text: "There is massive cost pressure on EVs in order to boost demand and to compete effectively with low-priced Chinese exports. There has been a “flood” of Chinese EVs in the European market
source_name: and they have gained 8% share of EVs sold with possible increase to 15% by 2025. Tesla has been forced to make a number of price cuts in 2023 which has reduced operating margin from 17.2% in the year-ago quarter to only 7.5% in the recent."
